<body><p>GE.<footnote name="1">13. Regarding the rights of older persons, Ms. Nunes mentioned the demographic 
changes in Brazil, to which the country must adapt with health policies, especially for older 
women, prevention of violence, and social security. She highlighted the National Plan and 
the National Council on the Rights of Older Persons, the holding of the National 
Conference in 2011, and the Statute of Older Persons. She also mentioned the social 
security programmes to ensure minimum income for all older persons in Brazil. </footnote>2-15115 
</p>
