open invitation to mandate holders. Iraq paid tribute to the country&#8217;s development policy 
and its various national human rights plans, particularly on the promotion of the rights of 
persons with disabilities. Iraq made recommendations. </footnote>18 4 
</p>
<p> II. Conclusions and/or recommendations .....................................................................  119&#8211;<footnote name="1">02. Iran acknowledged the efforts by Brazil to improve the standard of living of its 
people but voiced concern over reports of slave labour and discrimination against women.  
Iran made recommendations. 
</footnote>20 14 
